vg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104klb1688454363706.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/klb1688454363706.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/klb1688454363706.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"map1665702639139\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n EditBox\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"map1665702639139__editbox_369713\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\n </p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"map1665702639139__p_d112727e1_d112728e1_d112729e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"map1665702639139__fig_w8527ab1b5b3b1_w8528ab1b5b3_w8529ab1b5_w8530ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Editbox widget\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ueditbox.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"map1665702639139__table_d13412e1_d13413e1_d13414e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Logical widget name:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">EditBox</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Maps to physical widget:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ueditbox</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default definition:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">EditBox=ueditbox(font=editfont;autoselect=on;dimmedbackcolor=off)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported triggers and properties:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sgr1665702639069.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgr1665702639069.html\" title=\"The ueditbox widget is a field-level input control that enables the user to view and enter data in a field. It is applicable only to form components.\">ueditbox (EditBox)</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Use for:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Fields of any data type except Image.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\"> Supports Accessibility? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\"> Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more\n                     information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"abr1688541158363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abr1688541158363.html\" title=\"Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility).\">Accessibility</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"map1665702639139__topic_d79887e1_d79888e1_d79889e1_d79890e1_d79891e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d304959e177\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"map1665702639139__p_d112733e1_d112734e1_d112735e1\">The EditBox is the default widget used for component fields in forms and reports. If the field's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Type</span> is not specified, or if the specified widget type is not available at runtime for some reason, the EditBox logical widget is used.</p>\n<div class=\"div\"> </div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxx1665702627294.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Unifields</a><p>Unifields are field representations for displaying and entering data in character mode. They also work in Windows, but support only basic video attributes (bright, underline, inverse, and blink). They do not support proportional fonts or other properties.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399293\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399293\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "EditBox Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 EditBox Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report. Table 1. Widget Overview Logical widget name: EditBox Maps to physical widget: ueditbox Default definition: EditBox=ueditbox(font=editfont;autoselect=on;dimmedbackcolor=off) Supported triggers and properties: See ueditbox (EditBox) . Use for: Fields of any data type except Image. Supports Accessibility? Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more information, see Accessibility . Description The EditBox is the default widget used for component fields in forms and reports. If the field's Widget Type is not specified, or if the specified widget type is not available at runtime for some reason, the EditBox logical widget is used. Related Links Unifields Unifields are field representations for displaying and entering data in character mode. They also work in Windows, but support only basic video attributes (bright, underline, inverse, and blink). They do not support proportional fonts or other properties. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}